      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Method",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 3
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Mix and bake, 32 to 38 minutes",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Heat the oven to 170°C fan. Grease and line a 20 cm round cake tin. Sift together the {{plain-flour}}, {{cocoa-powder}}, {{caster-sugar}}, {{bicarbonate-of-soda}}, {{baking-powder}}, and {{fine-sea-salt}} into a large bowl. In a jug, combine the {{vegetable-oil}}, {{oat-milk}}, {{vanilla-extract}}, and {{apple-cider-vinegar}}. Pour the wet ingredients into the dry and whisk until smooth. Pour into the tin and bake for 32 to 38 minutes until a skewer inserted in the centre comes out clean. Cool in the tin for 15 minutes, then turn out onto a rack to cool completely.",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 3
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Make the ganache and finish",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Place the {{dark-chocolate}} in a heatproof bowl. Heat the {{coconut-cream}} in a small saucepan until it just begins to simmer, then pour over the chocolate. Leave for 2 minutes, then stir from the centre outward until smooth. Leave to cool at room temperature for 20 to 30 minutes until the ganache thickens to a pourable coating. Set the cooled cake on a rack over a tray and pour the ganache over the top, letting it run down the sides. Leave undisturbed for 30 minutes before cutting.",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      }
    ]
